tweets.author: Michigan409
tweets.content:
First RWA Integrated into Universal Data Feeds !
@Entanglefi
 has just launched ten precious metal price feeds as part of its Universal Data Feed (UDF), making it easier to integrate off-chain real-world data into blockchain applications. Here's what's included in the update:

- Gold (M-XAU)
- Silver (M-XAG)
- Platinum (M-XPT)
- Palladium (M-PXD)
- Zinc (M-ZNC)
- Aluminum (M-ALU)
- Uranium (M-URANIUM)
- LBMA Gold AM Fix (M-LBXAUAM)
- LBMA Gold PM Fix (M-LBXAUPM)
- LBMA Silver (M-LBXAG)

How It Works and What’s Coming Next:

- Seamless Integration : Entangle’s UDF streamlines the connection between off-chain, real-world data and blockchain smart contracts. Developers can focus on building functionality, without having to worry about data connectivity.

- Robust and Customizable Infrastructure : UDF ensures real-time, secure delivery of critical data to smart contracts, making it highly adaptable to different use cases.

- RWAs On-Chain : The framework enables issuers to bring off-chain data like market prices and proof of reserves onto the blockchain. This ensures that Real-World Assets (RWAs) are accurately represented and managed on-chain.

First RWAs and its just the beginning 

Stay tuned for more updates as Entangle continues to modify the future of RWAs and blockchain integration!
